{
  "doc_id": "59021",
  "text": "Although the parameter space for RPV spectra with sparticles below a TeV has recently been reduced, the sensitivity of these bounds is driven primarily by lepton number violating pro- cesses. For purely baryonic RPV, the bounds are considerably weaker and can accommodate natural stops with ∼ 100 GeV masses, provided they decay predominantly to dijets viaŪDD [CITATION_1] . For RPV gluinos decaying exclusively to g → t t, the strongest experimental bound is now ∼ > 670 GeV [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [32] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] , however, recasting R-parity conserving SUSY searches may place a stronger ∼ 800 GeV bound on the gluino mass [CITATION_7] .",
